fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The number of earlier messages from the chat to be forwarded to the new member; up to 300. Ignored for supergroups and channels.

addChatMember.desc:
Adds a new member to a chat. Members can't be added to private or secret chats. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: call_id
fields.desc: Description of the call protocols supported by the client.

acceptCall.desc:
Accepts an incoming call.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat.

addChatMembers.desc:
Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can't be used to join a chat. Members can't be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker file to add.

addFavoriteSticker.desc:
Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: entry
fields.desc: The network statistics entry with the data to be added to statistics.

addNetworkStatistics.desc:
Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to add.

addRecentlyFoundChat.desc:
Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: animation
fields.desc: The animation file to be added. Only animations known to the server (i.e. successfully sent via a message) can be added to the list.

addSavedAnimation.desc:
Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type "video/mp4" can be added to the list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Sticker file to add.

addRecentSticker.desc:
Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list.
Returns object_ptr<Stickers>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Sticker to add to the set.

addStickerToSet.desc:
Adds a new sticker to a set; for bots only. Returns the sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: callback_query_id
fields.desc: Time during which the result of the query can be cached, in seconds.

answerCallbackQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: custom_query_id
fields.desc: JSON-serialized answer to the query.

answerCustomQuery.desc:
Answers a custom query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: inline_query_id
fields.desc: The parameter for the bot start message.

answerInlineQuery.desc:
Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: pre_checkout_query_id
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerPreCheckoutQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: shipping_query_id
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerShippingQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of a file to stop downloading.

cancelDownloadFile.desc:
Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

blockUser.desc:
Adds a user to the blacklist.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to stop uploading.

cancelUploadFile.desc:
Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: If true, the chat will be reported as spam; otherwise it will be marked as not spam.

changeChatReportSpamState.desc:
Used to let the server know whether a chat is spam or not. Can be used only if ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam is true. After this request, ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam becomes false forever.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: contacts
fields.desc: The new list of contacts.

changeImportedContacts.desc:
Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time.
Returns object_ptr<ImportedContacts>.

fields.name: phone_number
fields.desc: Pass true if the phone number is used on the current device. Ignored if allow_flash_call is false.

changePhoneNumber.desc:
Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user's new phone number. On success, returns information about the sent code.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

fields.name: set_id
fields.desc: The new value of is_archived. A sticker set can't be installed and archived simultaneously.

changeStickerSet.desc:
Installs/uninstalls or activates/archives a sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The bot token.

checkAuthenticationBotToken.desc:
Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: If the user is not yet registered; the last name of the user; optional; 0-255 characters.

checkAuthenticationCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password to check.

checkAuthenticationPassword.desc:
Checks the authentication password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: invite_link
fields.desc: Invite link to be checked; should begin with "https://t.me/joinchat/", "https://telegram.me/joinchat/", or "https://telegram.dog/joinchat/".

checkChatInviteLink.desc:
Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLinkInfo>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code received by SMS, phone call or flash call.

checkChangePhoneNumberCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentlyFoundChats.desc:
Clears the list of recently found chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Pass true to clear the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to clear the list of recently sent stickers.

clearRecentStickers.desc:
Clears the list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearImportedContacts.desc:
Clears all imported contacts.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: encryption_key
fields.desc: Encryption key to check or set up.

checkDatabaseEncryptionKey.desc:
Checks the database encryption key for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEncryptionKey.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

close.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

closeChat.desc:
This method should be called if the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id
fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.

closeSecretChat.desc:
Closes a secret chat, effectively transfering its state to secretChatStateClosed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: basic_group_id
fields.desc: Basic group identifier.

createBasicGroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Description of the call protocols supported by the client.

createCall.desc:
Creates a new call.
Returns object_ptr<CallId>.

fields.name: user_ids
fields.desc: Title of the new basic group; 1-255 characters.

createNewBasicGroupChat.desc:
Creates a new basic group and sends a corresponding messageBasicGroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: List of stickers to be added to the set.

createNewStickerSet.desc:
Creates a new sticker set; for bots only. Returns the newly created sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the target user.

createNewSecretChat.desc:
Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Chat description; 0-255 characters.

createNewSupergroupChat.desc:
Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id
fields.desc: Secret Chat identifier.

createSecretChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known secret chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

createPrivateChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Supergroup or channel identifier.

createSupergroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: The reason why the account was deleted; optional.

deleteAccount.desc:
Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; should be between 60 and 86400.

createTemporaryPassword.desc:
Creates a new temporary password for processing payments.
Returns object_ptr<TemporaryPasswordState>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Pass true if the chat should be removed from the chats list.

deleteChatHistory.desc:
Deletes all messages in the chat only for the user. Cannot be used in channels and public supergroups.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

deleteChatMessagesFromUser.desc:
Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only in supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The message identifier of the used keyboard.

deleteChatReplyMarkup.desc:
Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Pass true to try to delete outgoing messages for all chat members (may fail if messages are too old). Always true for supergroups, channels and secret chats.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to delete.

deleteFile.desc:
Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: profile_photo_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the profile photo to delete.

deleteProfilePhoto.desc:
Deletes a profile photo. If something changes, updateUser will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedCredentials.desc:
Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedOrderInfo.desc:
Deletes saved order info.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the supergroup or channel.

deleteSupergroup.desc:
Deletes a supergroup or channel along with all messages in the corresponding chat. This will release the supergroup or channel username and remove all members; requires creator privileges in the supergroup or channel. Chats with more than 1000 members can't be deleted using this method.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

destroy.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: call_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the connection used during the call.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: New message content caption; 0-200 characters.

editInlineMessageCaption.desc:
Edits the caption of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile was called will be downloaded first.

downloadFile.desc:
Asynchronously downloads a file from the cloud. updateFile will be used to notify about the download progress and successful completion of the download. Returns file state just after the download has been started.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: New message reply markup.

editInlineMessageReplyMarkup.desc:
Edits the reply markup of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: New location content of the message; may be null. Pass null to stop sharing the live location.

editInlineMessageLiveLocation.desc:
Edits the content of a live location in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: New text content of the message. Should be of type InputMessageText.

editInlineMessageText.desc:
Edits the text of an inline text or game message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New message content caption; 0-200 characters.

editMessageCaption.desc:
Edits the message content caption. Non-bots can edit messages for a limited period of time. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New location content of the message; may be null. Pass null to stop sharing the live location.

editMessageLiveLocation.desc:
Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New text content of the message. Should be of type InputMessageText.

editMessageText.desc:
Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Non-bot users can edit messages for a limited period of time. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New message reply markup.

editMessageReplyMarkup.desc:
Edits the message reply markup; for bots only. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: True, if the messages should be grouped into an album after forwarding. For this to work, no more than 10 messages may be forwarded, and all of them must be photo or video messages.

forwardMessages.desc:
Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

generateChatInviteLink.desc:
Generates a new invite link for a chat; the previously generated link is revoked. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. In basic groups this can be called only by the group's creator; in supergroups and channels this requires appropriate administrator rights.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLink>.

fields.name: generation_id
fields.desc: If set, means that file generation has failed and should be terminated.

finishFileGeneration.desc:
Finishes the file generation.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: File identifier.

getAttachedStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file. Currently only photos and videos can have attached sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

getAccountTtl.desc:
Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<AccountTtl>.

getActiveLiveLocationMessages.desc:
Returns all active live locations that should be updated by the client. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

getActiveSessions.desc:
Returns all active sessions of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Sessions>.

fields.name: is_masks
fields.desc: Maximum number of sticker sets to return.

getArchivedStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of archived sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

fields.name: basic_group_id
fields.desc: Basic group identifier.

getBasicGroup.desc:
Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot.
Returns object_ptr<BasicGroup>.

fields.name: basic_group_id
fields.desc: Basic group identifier.

getBasicGroupFullInfo.desc:
Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier.
Returns object_ptr<BasicGroupFullInfo>.

getAuthorizationState.desc:
Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state.
Returns object_ptr<AuthorizationState>.

fields.name: offset
fields.desc: Maximum number of users to return; up to 100.

getBlockedUsers.desc:
Returns users that were blocked by the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Users>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

getChat.desc:
Returns information about a chat by its identifier, this is an offline request if the current user is not a bot.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

getChatAdministrators.desc:
Returns a list of users who are administrators of the chat.
Returns object_ptr<Users>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Query payload.

getCallbackQueryAnswer.desc:
Sends a callback query to a bot and returns an answer. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires.
Returns object_ptr<CallbackQueryAnswer>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: If true, returns only messages that are available locally without sending network requests.

getChatHistory.desc:
Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). This is an offline request if only_local is true.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

getChatMember.desc:
Returns information about a single member of a chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatMember>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: User identifiers by which to filter events. By default, events relating to all users will be returned.

getChatEventLog.desc:
Returns a list of service actions taken by chat members and administrators in the last 48 hours. Available only in supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights. Returns results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing event_id).
Returns object_ptr<ChatEvents>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages.

getChatMessageByDate.desc:
Returns the last message sent in a chat no later than the specified date.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: offset_order
fields.desc: The maximum number of chats to be returned. It is possible that fewer chats than the limit are returned even if the end of the list is not reached.

getChats.desc:
Returns an ordered list of chats. Chats are sorted by the pair (order, chat_id) in decreasing order. (For example, to get a list of chats from the beginning, the offset_order should be equal to 2^63 - 1.)
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

getChatReportSpamState.desc:
Returns information on whether the current chat can be reported as spam.
Returns object_ptr<ChatReportSpamState>.

getCreatedPublicChats.desc:
Returns a list of public chats created by the user.
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

fields.name: mime_type
fields.desc: The MIME type of the file.

getFileExtension.desc:
Returns the extension of a file, guessed by its MIME type. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. May be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

getGameHighScores.desc:
Returns the high scores for a game and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<GameHighScores>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to get.

getFile.desc:
Returns information about a file; this is an offline request.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

fields.name: file_name
fields.desc: The name of the file or path to the file.

getFileMimeType.desc:
Returns the MIME type of a file, guessed by its extension. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. May be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

getImportedContactCount.desc:
Returns the total number of imported contacts.
Returns object_ptr<Count>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 100.

getGroupsInCommon.desc:
Returns a list of common chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date.
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

getInlineGameHighScores.desc:
Returns game high scores and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<GameHighScores>.

fields.name: bot_user_id
fields.desc: Offset of the first entry to return.

getInlineQueryResults.desc:
Sends an inline query to a bot and returns its results. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires.
Returns object_ptr<InlineQueryResults>.

getMe.desc:
Returns the current user.
Returns object_ptr<User>.

getInviteText.desc:
Returns the default text for invitation messages to be used as a placeholder when the current user invites friends to Telegram.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

fields.name: is_masks
fields.desc: Pass true to return mask sticker sets; pass false to return ordinary sticker sets.

getInstalledStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of installed sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the message to get.

getMessage.desc:
Returns information about a message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: scope
fields.desc: Scope for which to return the notification settings information.

getNotificationSettings.desc:
Returns the notification settings for a given scope.
Returns object_ptr<NotificationSettings>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to get.

getMessages.desc:
Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the option.

getOption.desc:
Returns the value of an option by its name. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) This method can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<OptionValue>.

fields.name: only_current
fields.desc: If true, returns only data for the current library launch.

getNetworkStatistics.desc:
Returns network data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<NetworkStatistics>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Message identifier.

getPaymentReceipt.desc:
Returns information about a successful payment.
Returns object_ptr<PaymentReceipt>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the message.

getPublicMessageLink.desc:
Returns a public HTTPS link to a message. Available only for messages in public supergroups and channels.
Returns object_ptr<PublicMessageLink>.

getPasswordState.desc:
Returns the current state of 2-step verification.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Message identifier.

getPaymentForm.desc:
Returns an invoice payment form. This method should be called when the user presses inlineKeyboardButtonBuy.
Returns object_ptr<PaymentForm>.

getProxy.desc:
Returns the proxy that is currently set up. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Proxy>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Pass true to return stickers and masks that were recently attached to photos or video files; pass false to return recently sent stickers.

getRecentStickers.desc:
Returns a list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Stickers>.

fields.name: referrer
fields.desc: Google Play referrer to identify the user.

getRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.desc:
Returns t.me URLs recently visited by a newly registered user.
Returns object_ptr<TMeUrls>.

getRecentInlineBots.desc:
Returns up to 20 recently used inline bots in the order of their last usage.
Returns object_ptr<Users>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password for the current user.

getRecoveryEmailAddress.desc:
Returns a recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user.
Returns object_ptr<RecoveryEmailAddress>.

fields.name: remote_file_id
fields.desc: File type, if known.

getRemoteFile.desc:
Returns information about a file by its remote ID; this is an offline request. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

getSavedOrderInfo.desc:
Returns saved order info, if any.
Returns object_ptr<OrderInfo>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker file identifier.

getStickerEmojis.desc:
Returns emoji corresponding to a sticker.
Returns object_ptr<StickerEmojis>.

fields.name: emoji
fields.desc: Maximum number of stickers to be returned.

getStickers.desc:
Returns stickers from the installed sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji. If the emoji is not empty, favorite and recently used stickers may also be returned.
Returns object_ptr<Stickers>.

getStorageStatisticsFast.desc:
Quickly returns approximate storage usage statistics.
Returns object_ptr<StorageStatisticsFast>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id
fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.

getSecretChat.desc:
Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline request.
Returns object_ptr<SecretChat>.

fields.name: chat_limit
fields.desc: Maximum number of chats with the largest storage usage for which separate statistics should be returned. All other chats will be grouped in entries with chat_id == 0. If the chat info database is not used, the chat_limit is ignored and is always set to 0.

getStorageStatistics.desc:
Returns storage usage statistics.
Returns object_ptr<StorageStatistics>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Supergroup or channel identifier.

getSupergroup.desc:
Returns information about a supergroup or channel by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot.
Returns object_ptr<Supergroup>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: The maximum number of users be returned; up to 200.

getSupergroupMembers.desc:
Returns information about members or banned users in a supergroup or channel. Can be used only if SupergroupFullInfo.can_get_members == true; additionally, administrator privileges may be required for some filters.
Returns object_ptr<ChatMembers>.

fields.name: set_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set.

getStickerSet.desc:
Returns information about a sticker set by its identifier.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Supergroup or channel identifier.

getSupergroupFullInfo.desc:
Returns full information about a supergroup or channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute.
Returns object_ptr<SupergroupFullInfo>.

getSupportUser.desc:
Returns a user that can be contacted to get support.
Returns object_ptr<User>.

getTemporaryPasswordState.desc:
Returns information about the current temporary password.
Returns object_ptr<TemporaryPasswordState>.

getTermsOfService.desc:
Returns the terms of service. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

fields.name: text

getTextEntities.desc:
Returns all entities (mentions, hashtags, bot commands, URLs, and email addresses) contained in the text. This is an offline method. May be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<TextEntities>.

fields.name: category
fields.desc: Maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 30.

getTopChats.desc:
Returns a list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled.
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

getTrendingStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of trending sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

getUser.desc:
Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot.
Returns object_ptr<User>.

fields.name: setting
fields.desc: The privacy setting.

getUserPrivacySettingRules.desc:
Returns the current privacy settings.
Returns object_ptr<UserPrivacySettingRules>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Maximum number of photos to be returned; up to 100.

getUserProfilePhotos.desc:
Returns the profile photos of a user. The result of this query may be outdated: some photos might have been deleted already.
Returns object_ptr<UserProfilePhotos>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

getUserFullInfo.desc:
Returns full information about a user by their identifier.
Returns object_ptr<UserFullInfo>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

openChat.desc:
This method should be called if the chat is opened by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed (e.g., in supergroups and channels all updates are received only for opened chats).
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: If true, the full instant view for the web page will be returned.

getWebPageInstantView.desc:
Returns an instant view version of a web page if available. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no instant view page.
Returns object_ptr<WebPageInstantView>.

fields.name: message_text
fields.desc: Message text.

getWebPagePreview.desc:
Returns a web page preview by the text of the message. Do not call this function too often. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no preview.
Returns object_ptr<WebPage>.

fields.name: contacts
fields.desc: The list of contacts to import or edit.

importContacts.desc:
Adds new contacts or edits existing contacts; contacts' user identifiers are ignored.
Returns object_ptr<ImportedContacts>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: True, if there should be no notification about the pinned message.

pinSupergroupMessage.desc:
Pins a message in a supergroup or channel; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the message with the opened content.

openMessageContent.desc:
This method should be called if the message content has been opened (e.g., the user has opened a photo, video, document, location or venue, or has listened to an audio file or voice note message). An updateMessageContentOpened update will be generated if something has changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: invite_link
fields.desc: Invite link to import; should begin with "https://t.me/joinchat/", "https://telegram.me/joinchat/", or "https://telegram.dog/joinchat/".

joinChatByInviteLink.desc:
Uses an invite link to add the current user to the chat if possible. The new member will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

logOut.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: recovery_code
fields.desc: Recovery code to check.

recoverPassword.desc:
Recovers the password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.name: dc
fields.desc: Value of the "addr" parameter of the notification.

processDcUpdate.desc:
Handles a DC_UPDATE push service notification, can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

readAllChatMentions.desc:
Marks all mentions in a chat as read.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: recovery_code
fields.desc: Recovery code to check.

recoverAuthenticationPassword.desc:
Recovers the password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: device_token
fields.desc: Device token.

registerDevice.desc:
Registers the currently used device for receiving push notifications.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker file to delete from the list.

removeFavoriteSticker.desc:
Removes a sticker from the list of favorite stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: hashtag
fields.desc: Hashtag to delete.

removeRecentHashtag.desc:
Removes a hashtag from the list of recently used hashtags.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_ids
fields.desc: Identifiers of users to be deleted.

removeContacts.desc:
Removes users from the contacts list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: animation
fields.desc: Animation file to be removed.

removeSavedAnimation.desc:
Removes an animation from the list of saved animations.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to be removed.

removeRecentlyFoundChat.desc:
Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Sticker file to delete.

removeRecentSticker.desc:
Removes a sticker from the list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Same as in getStorageStatistics. Affects only returned statistics.

optimizeStorage.desc:
Optimizes storage usage, i.e. deletes some files and returns new storage usage statistics. Secret thumbnails can't be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<StorageStatistics>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker.

removeStickerFromSet.desc:
Removes a sticker from the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: category
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

removeTopChat.desc:
Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The reason for reporting the chat.

reportChat.desc:
Reports a chat to the Telegram moderators. Supported only for supergroups, channels, or private chats with bots, since other chats can't be checked by moderators.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_masks
fields.desc: Identifiers of installed sticker sets in the new correct order.

reorderInstalledStickerSets.desc:
Changes the order of installed sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery.desc:
Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

resendAuthenticationCode.desc:
Re-sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the next_code_type of the result is not null.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Identifiers of messages sent in the supergroup by the user. This list should be non-empty.

reportSupergroupSpam.desc:
Reports some messages from a user in a supergroup as spam.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

requestPasswordRecovery.desc:
Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordRecoveryInfo>.

resendChangePhoneNumberCode.desc:
Re-sends the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number for the user. Works only if the previously received authenticationCodeInfo next_code_type was not null.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resetAllNotificationSettings.desc:
Resets all notification settings to their default values. By default, the only muted chats are supergroups, the sound is set to "default" and message previews are shown.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: from_message_id
fields.desc: If true, returns only messages with missed calls.

searchCallMessages.desc:
Searches for call messages. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing message_id).
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

resetNetworkStatistics.desc:
Resets all network data usage statistics to zero. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Filter for message content in the search results.

searchChatMessages.desc:
Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query (searchSecretMessages should be used instead), or without an enabled message database.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The maximum number of users to be returned.

searchChatMembers.desc:
Searches for a specified query in the first name, last name and username of the members of a specified chat. Requires administrator rights in channels.
Returns object_ptr<ChatMembers>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Maximum number of messages to be returned.

searchChatRecentLocationMessages.desc:
Returns information about the recent locations of chat members that were sent to the chat. Returns up to 1 location message per user.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: Maximum number of chats to be returned.

searchChats.desc:
Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats, this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list.
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

fields.name: username
fields.desc: Username to be resolved.

searchPublicChat.desc:
Searches a public chat by its username. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise an error is returned.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: Maximum number of users to be returned.

searchContacts.desc:
Searches for the specified query in the first names, last names and usernames of the known user contacts.
Returns object_ptr<Users>.

fields.name: prefix
fields.desc: Maximum number of hashtags to be returned.

searchHashtags.desc:
Searches for recently used hashtags by their prefix.
Returns object_ptr<Hashtags>.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: Query to search for.

searchPublicChats.desc:
Searches public chats by a prefix of their username. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Returns nothing if the length of the searched username prefix is less than 5. Excludes private chats with contacts from the results.
Returns object_ptr<Chats>.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of the sticker set.

searchStickerSet.desc:
Searches for a sticker set by its short name.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: The maximum number of messages to be returned, up to 100.

searchMessages.desc:
Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)).
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: A filter for the content of messages in the search results.

searchSecretMessages.desc:
Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order.
Returns object_ptr<FoundMessages>.

fields.name: call_id
fields.desc: Debug information in application-specific format.

sendCallDebugInformation.desc:
Sends debug information for a call.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: bot_user_id
fields.desc: A hidden parameter sent to the bot for deep linking purposes (https://api.telegram.org/bots#deep-linking).

sendBotStartMessage.desc:
Invites a bot to a chat (if it is not yet a member) and sends it the /start command. Bots can't be invited to a private chat other than the chat with the bot. Bots can't be invited to channels (although they can be added as admins) and secret chats. Returns the sent message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: call_id
fields.desc: An optional user comment if the rating is less than 5.

sendCallRating.desc:
Sends a call rating.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The action description.

sendChatAction.desc:
Sends a notification about user activity in a chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

sendChatScreenshotTakenNotification.desc:
Sends a notification about a screenshot taken in a chat. Supported only in private and secret chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New TTL value, in seconds.

sendChatSetTtlMessage.desc:
Changes the current TTL setting (sets a new self-destruct timer) in a secret chat and sends the corresponding message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: method
fields.desc: JSON-serialized method parameters.

sendCustomRequest.desc:
Sends a custom request; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<CustomRequestResult>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the inline result.

sendInlineQueryResultMessage.desc:
Sends the result of an inline query as a message. Returns the sent message. Always clears a chat draft message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Contents of messages to be sent.

sendMessageAlbum.desc:
Sends messages grouped together into an album. Currently only photo and video messages can be grouped into an album. Returns sent messages.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The content of the message to be sent.

sendMessage.desc:
Sends a message. Returns the sent message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The credentials chosen by user for payment.

sendPaymentForm.desc:
Sends a filled-out payment form to the bot for final verification.
Returns object_ptr<PaymentResult>.

fields.name: ttl
fields.desc: New account TTL.

setAccountTtl.desc:
Changes the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: seconds
fields.desc: Number of seconds before the function returns.

setAlarm.desc:
Succeeds after a specified amount of time has passed. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: bio
fields.desc: The new value of the user bio; 0-70 characters without line feeds.

setBio.desc:
Changes the bio of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: phone_number
fields.desc: Pass true if the phone number is used on the current device. Ignored if allow_flash_call is false.

setAuthenticationPhoneNumber.desc:
Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: pending_update_count
fields.desc: The last error message.

setBotUpdatesStatus.desc:
Informs the server about the number of pending bot updates if they haven't been processed for a long time; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: The new status of the member in the chat.

setChatMemberStatus.desc:
Changes the status of a chat member, needs appropriate privileges. This function is currently not suitable for adding new members to the chat; instead, use addChatMember. The chat member status will not be changed until it has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New value of client_data.

setChatClientData.desc:
Changes client data associated with a chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New draft message; may be null.

setChatDraftMessage.desc:
Changes the draft message in a chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New chat photo. You can use a zero InputFileId to delete the chat photo. Files that are accessible only by HTTP URL are not acceptable.

setChatPhoto.desc:
Changes the photo of a chat. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights in basic groups and the appropriate administrator rights in supergroups and channels. The photo will not be changed before request to the server has been completed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: New title of the chat; 1-255 characters.

setChatTitle.desc:
Changes the chat title. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights in basic groups and the appropriate administrator rights in supergroups and channels. The title will not be changed until the request to the server has been completed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: new_encryption_key
fields.desc: New encryption key.

setDatabaseEncryptionKey.desc:
Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: generation_id
fields.desc: The number of bytes already generated.

setFileGenerationProgress.desc:
The next part of a file was generated.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Pass true to update the score even if it decreases. If the score is 0, the user will be deleted from the high score table.

setGameScore.desc:
Updates the game score of the specified user in the game; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: first_name
fields.desc: The new value of the optional last name for the user; 0-255 characters.

setName.desc:
Changes the first and last name of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: inline_message_id
fields.desc: Pass true to update the score even if it decreases. If the score is 0, the user will be deleted from the high score table.

setInlineGameScore.desc:
Updates the game score of the specified user in a game; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: scope
fields.desc: The new notification settings for the given scope.

setNotificationSettings.desc:
Changes notification settings for a given scope.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The new network type. By default, networkTypeOther.

setNetworkType.desc:
Sets the current network type. Can be called before authorization. Calling this method forces all network connections to reopen, mitigating the delay in switching between different networks, so it should be called whenever the network is changed, even if the network type remains the same. Network type is used to check whether the library can use the network at all and also for collecting detailed network data usage statistics.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: photo
fields.desc: Profile photo to set. inputFileId and inputFileRemote may still be unsupported.

setProfilePhoto.desc:
Uploads a new profile photo for the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The new value of the option.

setOption.desc:
Sets the value of an option. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Only writable options can be set. This method can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_ids
fields.desc: The new list of pinned chats.

setPinnedChats.desc:
Changes the order of pinned chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: old_password
fields.desc: New recovery email address; may be empty.

setPassword.desc:
Changes the password for the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the error EMAIL_UNCONFIRMED is returned and the password change will not be applied until the new recovery email address has been confirmed. The application should periodically call getPasswordState to check whether the new email address has been confirmed.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.name: proxy
fields.desc: Proxy server to use. Specify null to remove the proxy server.

setProxy.desc:
Sets the proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: New supergroup or channel description; 0-255 characters.

setSupergroupDescription.desc:
Changes information about a supergroup or channel; requires appropriate administrator rights.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: New recovery email address.

setRecoveryEmailAddress.desc:
Changes the recovery email address of the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the error EMAIL_UNCONFIRMED is returned and the email address will not be changed until the new email has been confirmed. The application should periodically call getPasswordState to check whether the email address has been confirmed. If new_recovery_email_address is the same as the email address that is currently set up, this call succeeds immediately and aborts all other requests waiting for an email confirmation.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: New position of the sticker in the set, zero-based.

setStickerPositionInSet.desc:
Changes the position of a sticker in the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: New value of the supergroup sticker set identifier. Use 0 to remove the supergroup sticker set.

setSupergroupStickerSet.desc:
Changes the sticker set of a supergroup; requires appropriate rights in the supergroup.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: username
fields.desc: The new value of the username. Use an empty string to remove the username.

setUsername.desc:
Changes the username of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: New value of the username. Use an empty string to remove the username.

setSupergroupUsername.desc:
Changes the username of the supergroup or channel, requires creator privileges in the supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: parameters
fields.desc: Parameters.

setTdlibParameters.desc:
Sets the parameters for TDLib initialization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: setting
fields.desc: The new privacy rules.

setUserPrivacySettingRules.desc:
Changes user privacy settings.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

terminateAllOtherSessions.desc:
Terminates all other sessions of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

testCallBytes.desc:
Returns the received bytes; for testing only.

fields.name: session_id

terminateSession.desc:
Terminates a session of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

testCallEmpty.desc:
Does nothing; for testing only.

testCallString.desc:
Returns the received string; for testing only.

fields.name: x

testCallVectorInt.desc:
Returns the received vector of numbers; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<TestVectorInt>.

fields.name: x

testCallVectorIntObject.desc:
Returns the received vector of objects containing a number; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<TestVectorIntObject>.

fields.name: x
fields.desc: Vector of strings to return.

testCallVectorString.desc:
For testing only request. Returns the received vector of strings; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<TestVectorString>.

fields.name: x
fields.desc: Vector of objects to return.

testCallVectorStringObject.desc:
Returns the received vector of objects containing a string; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<TestVectorStringObject>.

testGetDifference.desc:
Forces an updates.getDifference call to the Telegram servers; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

testNetwork.desc:
Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: x
fields.desc: Number to square.

testSquareInt.desc:
Returns the squared received number; for testing only.

testUseError.desc:
Does nothing and ensures that the Error object is used; for testing only.

fields.name: basic_group_id

toggleBasicGroupAdministrators.desc:
Toggles the "All members are admins" setting in basic groups; requires creator privileges in the group.

testUseUpdate.desc:
Does nothing and ensures that the Update object is used; for testing only.
Returns object_ptr<Update>.

toggleChatIsPinned.desc:
Changes the pinned state of a chat. You can pin up to GetOption("pinned_chat_count_max") non-secret chats and the same number of secret chats.

fields.desc: New value of anyone_can_invite.

toggleSupergroupInvites.desc:
Toggles whether all members of a supergroup can add new members; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: The new value of is_all_history_available.

toggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable.desc:
Toggles whether the message history of a supergroup is available to new members; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

upgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergroupChat.desc:
Creates a new supergroup from an existing basic group and sends a corresponding messageChatUpgradeTo and messageChatUpgradeFrom. Deactivates the original basic group.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: New value of sign_messages.

toggleSupergroupSignMessages.desc:
Toggles sender signatures messages sent in a channel; requires appropriate administrator rights in the channel.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_id

unblockUser.desc:
Removes a user from the blacklist.

uploadStickerFile.desc:

fields.desc: Identifier of the supergroup or channel.

unpinSupergroupMessage.desc:

fields.desc: Identifiers of viewed trending sticker sets.

viewTrendingStickerSets.desc:

authenticationCodeInfo.desc: Information about the authentication code that was sent.
